Turns https://sourceforge.net/projects/aper/ into sendmail access db
- Filters out blank lines
- Filters out comment lines
- Filters out lines without an @
- Filters out lines without an RHS
- Filters out lines without an LHS
- Filters out lines with our domain on the RHS
- Filters out arbitrary whitelisted addresses

awk -f aper.awk phishing_reply_addresses > access.aper

aper.sh does all of the above but also searches directory.yale.edu when it sees @yale.edu
aper.sh removes the whitelist feature

make -f test.mk can be used to compare old and new
